   "source": [
    "# 🚀 CSA GPU Benchmark - Google Colab\n",
    "\n",
    "**Compressed Speculative Attention - GPU Performance Testing**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook runs CSA benchmarks on GPU to measure:\n",
    "- KV cache compression effectiveness\n",
    "- Generation performance\n",
    "- Memory usage\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ **Requirements:**\n",
    "- GPU runtime (T4 or better)\n",
    "- ~8GB+ VRAM for GPT-2\n",
    "- ~16GB+ VRAM for larger models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Section 1: Setup & Verification"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check GPU availability\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n",
    "║         CSA GPU Benchmark Setup                      ║\n",
    "╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# GPU Information\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ GPU Available: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   CUDA Version: {torch.version.cuda}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Total Memory: {torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB\")\n",
    "    device = \"cuda\"\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ GPU Not Available - Switch to GPU runtime!\")\n",
    "    print(\"   Go to Runtime → Change runtime type → GPU\")\n",
    "    device = \"cpu\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDevice: {device}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install -q transformers accelerate psutil\n",
    "\n",
    "# If CSA not installed, install from current directory\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check if we're in CSA directory\n",
    "if Path('/content/csa').exists():\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, '/content')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    # Clone CSA if not present\n",
    "    !git clone https://github.com/kishoretvk/DevClaw.git\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, '/content/DevClaw')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Setup complete!\")\n",
    "print(f\"Python path: {sys.path[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import CSA modules\n",
    "from csa import CSAEngine\n",
    "from csa.compression import AttentionMatcher\n",
    "from csa.quantization import TurboQuantCache\n",
    "\n",
    "from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ CSA modules imported successfully\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Section 2: Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Benchmark Configuration\n",
    "CONFIG = {\n",
    "    \"model_name\": \"gpt2\",  # Change to \"gpt2-medium\" or larger for bigger tests\n",
    "    \"device\": device,\n",
    "    \"max_new_tokens\": 50,\n",
    "    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n",
    "    \"compression_ratio\": 50,\n",
    "    \"compression_frequency\": \"once\",\n",
    "    \"skip_compression_threshold\": 512,  # Must be >512 to trigger compression\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a LONG prompt to trigger compression (>512 tokens)\n",
    "# This is critical - short prompts skip compression!\n",
    "base_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
    "The future of artificial intelligence is a topic of great interest and debate. \n",
    "Many experts believe that AI will transform various industries including healthcare, \n",
    "education, transportation, and manufacturing. Machine learning algorithms are becoming \n",
    "more sophisticated every year, enabling new capabilities that were previously thought impossible. \n",
    "Neural networks with billions of parameters can now generate human-like text, recognize speech, \n",
    "and even create art. However, these advances come with challenges. The computational requirements \n",
    "for running large language models are substantial, requiring specialized hardware and significant \n",
    "energy consumption. Additionally, there are concerns about bias in AI systems, privacy implications, \n",
    "and the potential for misuse. Researchers are actively working on making AI more efficient, \n",
    "trustworthy, and accessible. Techniques like model compression, quantization, and speculative \n",
    "decoding aim to reduce the computational burden while maintaining performance. The goal is to \n",
    "democratize access to powerful AI tools so that they can benefit society as a whole. Looking ahead, \n",
    "we can expect continued innovation in areas like multimodal AI, reasoning capabilities, and \n",
",
    "longer context windows. The interaction between AI and other emerging technologies like quantum \n",
    "computing and biotechnology may lead to breakthroughs we cannot even imagine today. As we stand at \n",
    "the threshold of this new era, it is crucial that we approach AI development thoughtfully and \n",
    "responsibly, ensuring that the benefits are widely shared and the risks are properly managed. The \n",
    "path forward requires collaboration between researchers, policymakers, industry leaders, and the \n",
    "public to shape a future where AI serves humanity's best interests. This involves not only technical \n",
    "innovation but also careful consideration of ethical principles, social impact, and long-term \n",
    "consequences. The decisions we make today about AI development and deployment will have profound \n",
    "implications for generations to come. Therefore, it is essential to engage in open dialogue, \n",
    "establish robust governance frameworks, and invest in education to prepare society for an \n",
    "AI-enabled future.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify prompt length\n",
    "temp_tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(CONFIG[\"model_name\"])\n",
    "prompt_tokens = len(temp_tokenizer.encode(base_prompt))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Config:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Model: {CONFIG['model_name']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Device: {CONFIG['device']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Max new tokens: {CONFIG['max_new_tokens']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Compression ratio: {CONFIG['compression_ratio']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPrompt length: {prompt_tokens} tokens\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if prompt_tokens < CONFIG['skip_compression_threshold']:\n",
    "    print(f\"⚠️  WARNING: Prompt is too short! Need >{CONFIG['skip_compression_threshold']} tokens\")\n",
    "    print(\"   Compression will be SKIPPED!\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Prompt length OK (> {CONFIG['skip_compression_threshold']})\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Compression WILL trigger\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Section 3: Baseline Benchmark\n",
    "\n",
    "Standard generation without CSA compression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_gpu_memory():\n",
    "    \"\"\"Get current GPU memory in MB.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "        return torch.cuda.memory_allocated() / 1024 / 1024\n",
    "    return 0\n",
    "\n",
    "def baseline_benchmark(config, prompt):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Run baseline without CSA.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "    print(\"BASELINE: Standard Generation (No Compression)\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Clear cache\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Load model\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nLoading {config['model_name']}...\")\n",
    "    model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
    "        config['model_name'],\n",
    "        torch_dtype=torch.float16,\n",
    "        device_map=\"auto\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(config['model_name'])\n",
    "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Prepare input\n",
    "    input_ids = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model.device)\n",
    "    print(f\"Input tokens: {input_ids.input_ids.shape[1]}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Measure memory before\n",
    "    mem_before = get_gpu_memory()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nGenerating {config['max_new_tokens']} tokens...\")\n",
    "    start_time = time.time()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        output = model.generate(\n",
    "            input_ids.input_ids,\n",
    "            max_new_tokens=config['max_new_tokens'],\n",
    "            do_sample=True,\n",
    "            temperature=config['temperature'],\n",
    "            pad_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    elapsed = time.time() - start_time\n",
    "    mem_after = get_gpu_memory()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Decode result\n",
    "    generated_ids = output[0][input_ids.input_ids.shape[1]:]\n",
    "    text = tokenizer.decode(generated_ids, skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Cleanup\n",
    "    del model\n",
    "    del tokenizer\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result = {\n",
    "        \"time\": elapsed,\n",
    "        \"memory_mb\": mem_after - mem_before,\n",
    "        \"tokens_per_sec\": len(generated_ids) / elapsed,\n",
    "        \"tokens_generated\": len(generated_ids),\n",
    "        \"text\": text[:200] + \"...\" if len(text) > 200 else text\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✅ Baseline Complete:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Time: {result['time']:.2f}s\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Memory: {result['memory_mb']:.0f} MB\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Speed: {result['tokens_per_sec']:.1f} tokens/s\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Tokens: {result['tokens_generated']}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return result\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run baseline\n",
    "baseline_results = baseline_benchmark(CONFIG, base_prompt)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Section 4: CSA Benchmark\n",
    "\n",
    "Generation with CSA compression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def csa_benchmark(config, prompt):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Run benchmark with CSA.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "    print(\"CSA: Compressed Speculative Attention\"\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Clear cache\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Initialize CSA\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nLoading CSA Engine...\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Compression ratio: {config['compression_ratio']}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    engine = CSAEngine(\n",
    "        config['model_name'],\n",
    "        compression_ratio=config['compression_ratio'],\n",
    "        compression_frequency=config['compression_frequency'],\n",
    "        skip_compression_threshold=config['skip_compression_threshold'],\n",
    "        use_speculation=False  # Simple mode for testing\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Measure memory before\n",
    "    mem_before = get_gpu_memory()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate with profiling\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nGenerating {config['max_new_tokens']} tokens...\")\n",
    "    start_time = time.time()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    text = engine.generate(\n",
    "        prompt,\n",
    "        max_new_tokens=config['max_new_tokens'],\n",
    "        enable_profiling=True\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    elapsed = time.time() - start_time\n",
    "    mem_after = get_gpu_memory()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Cleanup\n",
    "    del engine\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "        torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result = {\n",
    "        \"time\": elapsed,\n",
    "        \"memory_mb\": mem_after - mem_before,\n",
    "        \"tokens_per_sec\": config['max_new_tokens'] / elapsed,\n",
    "        \"text\": text[:200] + \"...\" if len(text) > 200 else text\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✅ CSA Complete:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Time: {result['time']:.2f}s\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Memory: {result['memory_mb']:.0f} MB\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Speed: {result['tokens_per_sec']:.1f} tokens/s\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return result\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run CSA\n",
    "csa_results = csa_benchmark(CONFIG, base_prompt)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Section 5: Results Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare results\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"COMPARISON RESULTS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{'Metric':<25} {'Baseline':>15} {'CSA':>15} {'Change':>10}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 65)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Time\n",
    "time_change = (csa_results['time'] - baseline_results['time']) / baseline_results['time'] * 100\n",
    "time_color = \"🟢\" if time_change < -10 else (\"🔴\" if time_change > 10 else \"🟡\")\n",
    "print(f\"{time_color} {'Time (s)':<23} {baseline_results['time']:>15.2f}{csa_results['time']:>15.2f}{time_change:>+9.1f}%\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Memory\n",
    "mem_baseline = baseline_results['memory_mb']\n",
    "mem_csa = csa_results['memory_mb']\n",
    "if mem_baseline > 0:\n",
    "    mem_change = (mem_csa - mem_baseline) / mem_baseline * 100\n",
    "    mem_color = \"🟢\" if mem_change < -10 else (\"🔴\" if mem_change > 10 else \"🟡\")\n",
    "    print(f\"{mem_color} {'Memory (MB)':<23} {mem_baseline:>15.0f}{mem_csa:>15.0f}{mem_change:>+9.1f}%\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"{'Memory (MB)':<25} {mem_baseline:>15.0f}{mem_csa:>15.0f}{'N/A':>10}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speed (tokens/sec)\n",
    "speed_change = (csa_results['tokens_per_sec'] - baseline_results['tokens_per_sec']) / baseline_results['tokens_per_sec'] * 100\n",
    "speed_color = \"🟢\" if speed_change > 10 else (\"🔴\" if speed_change < -10 else \"🟡\")\n",
    "print(f\"{speed_color} {'Speed (tok/s)':<23} {baseline_results['tokens_per_sec']:>15.1f}{csa_results['tokens_per_sec']:>15.1f}{speed_change:>+9.1f}%\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokens\n",
    "print(f\"{'Tokens Generated':<25} {baseline_results['tokens_generated']:>15}{CONFIG['max_new_tokens']:>15}{'--':>10}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"KEY OBSERVATIONS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "\n",
    "if time_change < -10:\n",
    "    print(\"✓ CSA is faster than baseline\")\n",
    "elif time_change > 10:\n",
    "    print(\"⚠ CSA is slower than baseline\")\n",
    "    print(\"  Note: This is expected with current implementation\")\n",
    "    print(\"  Compressed cache is computed but not used during generation\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"○ Similar performance\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n💾 Compression was triggered: {'Yes' if len(base_prompt) > 500 else 'No (prompt too short)'}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
